Dri-Fit science for parents that may not know : Dri-Fir has been proven (a long time ago) , to be so good at doing what it claims (wicking moisture away from the body) that it actually makes the body work 25% harder to cool itself. When sweat (which our bodies use to cool off) is wicked away at such an impressive rate, our bodies actually go into a hyperactive mode trying to cool ourselves off. Dri fit is great. But just be aware of this (especially in high heat or high energy activities ). It can lead to heat stroke , heat stress etc. @sportscience did a thing way back on it. Super fascinating. Anyways. If that saves 1 kid, or parent. It was worth the type. That being said I wear dri-fit, but not in high energy or high heat scenarios anymore.
